div.p:
An examination of the Log of the U. S. S. Guam for July
                    11, 1933, shows that the following foreign government vessels were at Hankow on
                    that date: 

H. M. S. Bee, Cumberland, Falcon, Aphis, Gannet;


R. F. S. Algov, Francis Gamier, H. I. J. M. S. Hodga;


R. C. S. Yung Sui, Teh Sheng, Weh Sheng.
